    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>Albany</placeName>
                <add>בין כסה לעשור תורי' לב"ק</add>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">A young man perfectly<lb/> qualified to impart instruction in
                    <sic>english</sic><lb/> spelling, reading, writing, grammar etc can<lb/> find an
                ample opportunity in my house to<lb/> educate himself for the <sic>hebrew</sic>
                ministry.<lb/> He finds here a Synagogue with a well instruc<lb/>ted choir, where he
                can prepare himself<lb/> for the chasanship; a great, well regulated<lb/> school to
                finish his education as a teacher;<lb/> to finish his education as a preacher and in<lb/>
                <sic>hebrew</sic> scholarship I offer him a large <sic>liberary</sic>*<lb/> and my
                assistance. If you have a young<lb/> man to <sic>recommand</sic>, he shall be very
                welcome<lb/> to me.</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">I am respectfully yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Rabbi Wise</persName> D D</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <placeName>134 S. Pearl St.</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
